$ Script: p8

`p8` is intended to quickly find out if there is a connection to the internet.

The script pings → Companies-Products/Google[Google's] public DNS server which is located on the IP address 8.8.8.8.

It comes in three variants:
  • Linux shell script (`p8`)
  • → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files[Windows batch file] (`p8.bat`)
  • → Windows/PowerShell script (`p8.ps`)


{ p8

  gh|scripts-and-utilities|/p8||

}
{ p8.bat #p8-bat

  The Windows batch file variant uses → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/PING_EXE[`ping.exe`]

  gh|scripts-and-utilities|/p8.bat||

}
